      • DefaultAddMode

      • NO_DUPS

        public static final int NO_DUPS
        throw an exception if a duplicate object is added. This is Default. see HubController#setAddMode
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • IGNORE_DUPS

        public static final int IGNORE_DUPS
        dont store object if a duplicate is already stored. If the object is being deserialized (see OAObject.readResolve) then the object that is already loaded will be used. see HubController#setAddMode
        See Also:
        OAObject.readResolve(), Constant Field Values

      • OVERWRITE_DUPS

        public static final int OVERWRITE_DUPS
        store object even if another exists see HubController#setAddMode
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

        public static final int IGNORE_ALL
        dont store objects. see HubController#setAddMode

        public static Hub[] getSelectAllHubs(Class clazz)

      • setDefaultAddMode

        public static void setDefaultAddMode(int mode)
        The DefaultAddMode determines how HubController.addObject() will handle an object if it already exists. This method sets the Default mode for all unassigned threads.
        Parameters:
        mode - AddModes are NO_DUPS (default), IGNORE_DUPS, OVERWRITE_DUPS. see HubController#setAddMode

      • _find

        protected static Object _find(Object fromObject,
                              Class clazz,
                              String propertyPath,
                              Object findValue,
                              boolean bSkipNew,
                              boolean bThrowException,
                              int fetchAmount,
                              ArrayList<Object> alResults)
        Returns objects from the objectCache.
        Parameters:
        clazz - type of objects
        fromObject - null to start from the beginning, else use the last object previously returned.
        fetchAmount - max number to add to the alResults
        alResults - list of objects, after the fromObject
        Returns:
        last object in alResults, that can be used as the fromObject on the next call to fetch

      • refresh

        public static void refresh(Class clazz)
        Refresh all objects from the datasource. This will be ran on the server, if called by client then it will async to run on server.
        Parameters:
        clazz - Class of objects to update, will also requery all hubs for this class.
